data.title: Paul Randolph
data.meta_description: Paul Randolph coached defensive ends at Alabama for three seasons, helping the Tide lead the nation in scoring defense in 2005.
data.text:
Paul Randolph coached defensive ends at Alabama from 2003-05, helping the Tide lead the nation in scoring defense his last season in Tuscaloosa.

Most recently, he has served as the associate head coach and co-defensive coordinator for Arizona State under Todd Graham. Randolph also worked under Graham at Pittsburgh and Rice.

Randolphâ€™s other college stops as a coach include Tulane, West Virginia, Toledo, Illinois State, Valdosta State and his alma mater, Tennessee-Martin.
